<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1773] Infinite loop caused by race condition</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1773</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.avro.LogicalTypes#fromSchemaIgnoreInvalid lookups and update  CACHE. CACHE is backed by hashmap without synchronization. In a multithreaded environment, it causes a infinite loop in hashmap lookup. The race condition problem is described in the following blog &lt;a href=&quot;http://mailinator.blogspot.com/2009/06/beautiful-race-condition.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mailinator.blogspot.com/2009/06/beautiful-race-condition.html&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I experience this infinite loop in Spark jobs with high concurrency.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
